\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Reasonable elaborations or intermediate inferences by themselves are not errors.

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYGZdq{}uncertain\PYGZdq{}:
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The case is borderline and it is genuinely unclear whether the differences materially affect downstream usability.

Additional integrated guidelines:
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Prefer usability over perfection.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Do not over\PYGZhy{}penalize alternative but reasonable reasoning decompositions.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Be strict only when issues affect faithfulness, meaning preservation, reasoning\PYGZhy{}chain quality, or downstream usefulness.

